5: Does life get any better than this?
7:
Ever since I got the ability to sense
the dead's lingering thoughts, I've
been gathering tons of crazy info at
a great rate! I'm making bank!
11:
...Yeah, and because of that, I've
been getting complaints nonstop.
15:
Your schemes are causing big
problems, and for some reason, the
Guild's been sending their
grievances my way!
22:
Gosh, that's terrible. Anyway, I need
you to help me with a job!
26:
So I'm going to make dinner now.
You don't get any, by the way.
30:
I promise that this time we're doing
a good deed! Or are you telling me
you'd rather let a cheater run free
and run rampant?
33:
I'd rather not get involved in some
stranger's messy drama, thanks.
36:
You sure? The guy's name is Deiter,
and he's a two-timing lousy rich
loser.
43:
Ah, so you've heard of him? He's
been in the spotlight lately for some
pretty underhanded dealings.
45:
Loves abusing kids too. A guy like
that deserves to be exposed for his
dirty deeds, don't you think?
49:
...If you make me work for free again,
I swear I'm not making any dinner
for you.
54:
Me, cheat? Either you're stupid, or
you're a liar. Maybe both.
57:
Why don't you cut the act? I've got
proof, you know.
62:
I borrowed it from your secretary.
Poor taste to make someone else
buy your gift for you, by the way.
65:
Anyway, you're not getting out of
this. But don't worry. I'm not here on
behalf of your wife. I'm here to strike
a deal.
67: You know what I'm getting at.
70:
What, you wanna blackmail me for
money? I already considered that
risk from the get-go.
71:
I've got contacts in the Guild who'd
be more than happy to put a
wannabe informant like you in his
place.
74: Oh wow, I guess I'm in a pickle, huh?
79:
Think about it for a moment. That
secretary of yours is already long
gone from this world, remember?
83:
Bought property illegally, then killed
herself when he got found out. What
a tragedy, huh?
85:
You know what he told me? "He
forced me to do it all. I couldn't take
it anymore."
88:
Y-you think you can scare me with
crap like that?!
91:
He wasn't the only one that had a
bone to pick either. Can't you hear
her? "Even though I loved him... I
won't forgive him."
94:
Did you think it'd all go away if you
killed everyone? Gosh,
heavy-handed people like you are
so silly! Makes my job easier though.
97:
Damn it... Who in the hell are you?
One of the real estate punks?
99:
Me, one of them? That's just
insulting. Your first guess was
correct.
102:
I AM an informantone that's so
special he can commune with the
dead.
105:
Anyway, I bet the papers would
have a field day if I told them all I
know about you.
108: But you don't want that, right?
111:
Why, you... You little brat! How dare
you mess with me!
113:
Kill him! What's another body or two
at this point?!
117:
...Is this how you killed those other
poor souls?
122:
Relaaaax. It's not like I want to kill
you.
125:
I just want us to have a long and
fruitful relationship.
130:
Whew, I just made a killing off that!
The job was nice and easy to boot!
134:
...Are you seriously going to protect
that guy?
137:
Well, yeah. If I left him alone, he'd
die. For real.
140:
Do you wanna hear about what my
actual job was this time? I bet you're
curious about the client too.
147: Well, well. Fancy seeing you here, Alk.
150: Oh... Zekhel... What're you doing here?
153:
Came to drop off my report. Just got
back from dealing with some stuff
regarding the purchase of an
orphanage's plot of land.
156:
Turns out the guy behind it was
pulling some illegal moves. We
managed to put him in chains... But
you don't seem surprised.
159:
Well... Let's just say I've got my
sources.
162:
Then I guess you already know that
Deiter's the one that did it, and on
top of murder and other charges,
he's never leaving prison.
165:
Funnily enough, the guy kept cursing
someone named Shion when we
brought him in...
168:
Better be careful when you play with
fire. A step too far, and there's no
coming back from it.
172:
...So Deiter lives while he's in custody
of the Guild, and the orphanage is
saved.
175:
Everyone lives happily ever after.
That's what you wanted, right?
Consider this happy ending your
reward!
178:
Isn't this great? Not only did I get
something out of this, but you did
too!
182:
How is it that you can ruin even a
good thing...
187:
Hey, why don't you help me out with
another job? I need to deliver a
letter.
